Class ErrorPage

java.lang.Object
org.springframework.boot.web.error.ErrorPage
public class ErrorPage extends Object
Simple server-independent abstraction for error pages. Roughly equivalent to the &lt;error-page&gt; element traditionally found in web.xml.
Since:
4.0.0
Author:
Dave Syer

    • getPath

      public String getPath()
      The path to render (usually implemented as a forward), starting with "/". A custom controller or servlet path can be used, or if the server supports it, a template path (e.g. "/error.jsp").
      Returns:
      the path that will be rendered for this error

    • getStatusCode

      public int getStatusCode()
      The HTTP status value that this error page matches.
